Job Description:
• Lead the establishment and functions of the Intercon Rooster, which is the company’s monthly newsletter in English and Khmer;
• Develop a strategic plan and business plan for the functioning of the Intercon Rooster as a leading Khmer-English newspaper in the future;
• Manage the day-to-day operations and the monthly publication of the newsletter;
• Form a team of staff writers, ensuring adequate team members to produce and release each issue on time;
• Provide guidelines to staff writers for writing and submitting the articles;
• Establish a system of quick and effective peer review and ensure all staff writers communicate and provide feedback/comments in a professional and constructive manner;
• Establish clear guidelines for staff writers ensuring that they adhere to journalist ethics and clearly communicate all editorial and publication policies and acceptable practices to all staff writers and concerned stakeholders;
• Review all articles, photographs and all other publishing materials in the Intercon Rooster for accuracy, objectiveness and integrity in both hard and digital copy;
• Approve the layout and design of the newsletter;
• Meet and report regularly to the publisher and the publication board to discuss issues, plans and other business related to the publication.;
• Be innovative in generating new ideas and ways in improving the newsletter including increasing its circulation and readership and using new technology;
• Act as the representative of the Intercon Rooster in all social functions both inside and outside the country;
• Be aware of the responsibilities toward the publisher, reviewers, readers, scientific community, and the public at large.

